Are you?

02:57.089 --> 02:59.485
No, it's okay.

02:59.487 --> 03:01.423
Really, it's fine.

03:01.419 --> 03:04.114
I just couldn't <i> not</i> tell them.
You know?

03:04.116 --> 03:06.851
I know.

03:06.848 --> 03:09.273
I mean,
I just get so excited.

03:09.278 --> 03:12.442
<i> Am</i> excited. Happy.

03:15.606 --> 03:18.001
I'm glad, teddy.
Me too.

03:18.003 --> 03:19.261
Yeah?

03:21.866 --> 03:24.890
Of course I am.

03:24.897 --> 03:28.560
Getting excited
a little bit.

03:28.561 --> 03:30.897
I mean, god's will, right?

03:31.989 --> 03:34.085
Yes.

03:46.110 --> 03:49.504
I love you, tawney.

03:49.508 --> 03:52.332
I know you do.

03:52.338 --> 03:54.434
I love you, too.

03:56.334 --> 03:57.901
Do you?

03:57.901 --> 04:01.294
I do love you, teddy.

04:21.444 --> 04:24.069
Jesus.

04:24.076 --> 04:27.829
How'd you even know
where I lived?

04:27.839 --> 04:30.294
White pages.

04:30.303 --> 04:32.769
oh, yeah.

04:32.769 --> 04:34.406
Those.

04:37.096 --> 04:41.827
It's amazing what survives
and what doesn't, isn't it?

04:41.826 --> 04:43.194
It is.

04:43.192 --> 04:46.885
Well, shit.

04:46.889 --> 04:49.524
What can I do for you,
daniel?

04:49.520 --> 04:53.412
I'm not sure
why today exactly,

04:53.416 --> 04:55.981
But, uh...

04:55.980 --> 04:58.176
I wanted to come
and see you.

04:58.178 --> 05:00.414
Is that right?

05:00.410 --> 05:03.035
To say
"no hard feelings."

05:03.041 --> 05:05.336
All right.

05:05.338 --> 05:07.863
Sure, buddy.

05:07.869 --> 05:09.137
Thanks.

05:12.897 --> 05:15.392
You huff it
all the way over here?

05:17.792 --> 05:19.759
It's not that far.

05:19.759 --> 05:21.725
Not that close, either.

05:23.154 --> 05:25.749
Got anyplace else
you're supposed to be?

05:29.016 --> 05:31.880
Then get your ass
on inside.

05:52.461 --> 05:55.026
Did they give you
grape soda?

05:55.026 --> 05:56.353
Who?

05:56.358 --> 05:57.955
The police.

05:57.956 --> 06:00.012
That night.

06:00.021 --> 06:02.357
"that night"?

06:04.018 --> 06:07.311
Well, damn, daniel,
you just jumping right in, huh?

06:08.812 --> 06:11.946
I'm not even sure, man.

06:11.943 --> 06:16.035
I don't think on it too much
anymore.

06:16.040 --> 06:17.777
Okay.

06:34.422 --> 06:36.089
You thirsty?

06:37.986 --> 06:41.819
My wife got these
for a church thing
she had over here.

06:41.816 --> 06:44.241
They've been
clogging up the fridge.

06:44.247 --> 06:46.104
I figure,
hey, it's Monday morning.

06:46.113 --> 06:48.109
Might as well have
an adult lemonade.

06:58.766 --> 07:01.801
We played tecmo bowl
on this.

07:01.798 --> 07:03.794
You're damn right
we did.

07:03.796 --> 07:05.163
Yeah.

07:05.161 --> 07:07.387
My parents gave it to us
when we got married.

07:07.393 --> 07:09.249
It anchors the room.

07:09.257 --> 07:12.222
So, uh...

07:12.222 --> 07:14.158
What was it like
in there, man?

07:15.884 --> 07:18.319
I mean, I got to ask.
Right?

07:18.316 --> 07:20.082
Confining.

07:20.081 --> 07:21.609
Mm.

07:21.614 --> 07:24.608
That would be the word for it,
I suppose.

07:24.611 --> 07:28.334
Confining in some ways,
but...

07:28.341 --> 07:30.676
Do you still talk
to george?

07:31.769 --> 07:33.935
Damn, that's a sequitur.

07:33.935 --> 07:35.262
George?

07:35.267 --> 07:36.864
George.

07:36.865 --> 07:38.802
I haven't seen
old george in...

07:38.798 --> 07:43.788
Well, we went fishing together
a couple years ago on the flint.

07:43.793 --> 07:45.949
Funny you mention him,
though.

07:45.958 --> 07:49.092
Thought I might
give him a call.

07:49.088 --> 07:53.250
Thought you'd give him a call
or you <i> gave</i> him a call?

07:53.251 --> 07:55.017
Easy there, counselor.

07:55.015 --> 07:57.880
Don't go poking me in the chest
with no question marks.

07:57.880 --> 07:59.946
I gave him a call.

07:59.945 --> 08:01.272
To be nice.

08:01.276 --> 08:04.840
Hadn't heard back.

08:04.840 --> 08:07.734
Where's he live now?

08:07.737 --> 08:09.993
Oh, these are terrible.
You want a beer?

08:11.067 --> 08:15.827
Uh...
Georgey lives in florida.

08:17.094 --> 08:19.260
Live oak.

08:19.260 --> 08:22.224
Satan's butthole, man.

08:25.587 --> 08:28.252
You ain't thinking
about hurting him, are you?

08:30.749 --> 08:33.284
I don't want to hurt
<i> anybody.</i>

08:33.280 --> 08:36.943
'cause I wouldn't want to be
a part of anything like that.

08:36.943 --> 08:38.700
Part of what?

08:38.707 --> 08:42.801
But if you go visit him,
tell him I said "hello."

08:46.002 --> 08:47.540
I will.

08:47.535 --> 08:50.858
Go visit him
or tell him I said "hello"?

08:54.294 --> 08:56.290
Both, I suppose.

08:56.293 --> 08:58.788
I'm not sure.

08:58.790 --> 09:01.614
I should go.

09:03.851 --> 09:06.177
Hey. Hey,
that's, uh...[chuckles]

09:06.184 --> 09:08.719
That's a long ride
down to live oak, buddy.

09:08.715 --> 09:10.212
I'll figure it out.

09:10.213 --> 09:12.748
I'll tell you what.

09:12.744 --> 09:14.072
Hey.

09:17.239 --> 09:19.635
I'm supposed to be
at a job this morning,

09:19.638 --> 09:22.133
But he's a cheap
son of a bitch, really.

09:22.135 --> 09:26.197
What say...
We go on a road trip?

09:26.198 --> 09:28.025
Should we call him first?

09:28.030 --> 09:30.994
Look, that night --

09:30.994 --> 09:33.629
Or that morning, I mean,
with the police --

09:33.625 --> 09:37.747
All I did was say
you and her were arguing.

09:37.754 --> 09:39.511
That's it.

09:39.520 --> 09:40.887
It was george who said --

09:41.816 --> 09:43.643
Hell.

09:43.649 --> 09:45.914
You want to go down
there, you want to talk
with him about it,

09:45.913 --> 09:49.546
As long as you keep it
gentlemanly...

09:51.509 --> 09:54.004
...I am happy
to do the driving.

09:57.968 --> 09:59.465
All right.

09:59.468 --> 10:01.694
Put your little bicycle
in the bed there,

10:01.699 --> 10:03.126
And you grab shotgun.

10:03.131 --> 10:05.028
I'm gonna piss real quick.

10:05.030 --> 10:07.465
And then
we'll hit the road, son!

11:09.637 --> 11:12.401
Tray tables up,
passengers.

11:12.401 --> 11:14.697
Prepare for takeoff.

11:36.944 --> 11:38.142
Oh.

11:38.144 --> 11:39.771
I-I got one for that.

11:39.776 --> 11:41.902
Figured you might.

11:46.536 --> 11:48.742
Your total is $41.20.

11:51.397 --> 11:52.855
One...

11:52.864 --> 11:54.930
Two...

11:54.929 --> 11:56.895
Three...

11:56.893 --> 11:59.488
Four...

12:00.689 --> 12:03.024
Five...

12:03.021 --> 12:06.654
Six...

12:06.651 --> 12:08.408
Seven...

12:08.416 --> 12:10.642
Eight $1s.

12:11.845 --> 12:14.041
Oh, there's that $10.

12:14.044 --> 12:15.701
Yep. There it is.

12:15.710 --> 12:18.474
And...$20.

12:18.473 --> 12:19.811
That's...
$38.

12:19.806 --> 12:21.433
$38?

12:21.438 --> 12:24.372
So I'm...
$3.20 short.

12:24.368 --> 12:25.366
$3.20...?

12:25.367 --> 12:26.665
Short.

12:30.330 --> 12:33.424
I hate to use these,
but...

12:34.924 --> 12:37.449
I don't even know
if that --

12:42.052 --> 12:44.448
Uh...

12:44.450 --> 12:46.675
You still owe 20 cents.

12:48.545 --> 12:50.711
I know I have a quarter
in here.

12:51.909 --> 12:54.774
It's a virginia one.
Got jamestown on it.

12:54.774 --> 12:57.538
Forget it.
God. Forget it.

12:57.537 --> 12:59.633
I will pay the 20 cents.
Not a problem, okay?

13:09.726 --> 13:11.523
What do you know?

13:11.525 --> 13:13.321
Jamestown.

13:19.051 --> 13:21.776
That's right --
right there.

13:24.678 --> 13:26.774
Appreciate you
flipping the bill for those.

13:26.777 --> 13:27.975
Tastes good.

13:27.976 --> 13:31.599
Yeah,
as good as it gets.

13:36.901 --> 13:39.895
Oh, man. Unreal.

13:39.898 --> 13:42.333
I mean, damn!
What?

13:42.329 --> 13:43.857
You son of a bitch!

13:43.862 --> 13:45.918
When I got out of bed
this morning

13:45.927 --> 13:49.390
And I was staring out
that little window
above our commode

13:49.390 --> 13:51.725
At the traffic light
that's out on 39

13:51.721 --> 13:54.746
That is always green
out beyond the hayfield,

13:54.752 --> 13:56.778
I never would have said,
"well, today's the day

13:56.783 --> 13:59.877
That I'm gonna go to florida
with daniel g.D. Holden."

13:59.880 --> 14:01.477
I mean, never.

14:02.977 --> 14:04.903
The light's always green?

14:04.909 --> 14:07.644
I ain't never seen it red.

14:07.640 --> 14:08.937
Not once.

14:08.938 --> 14:10.435
Why's it there?

14:10.437 --> 14:12.404
Hmm.

14:14.233 --> 14:16.359
Some things,
you just don't see coming.

14:17.697 --> 14:19.393
I think you're right.

14:19.395 --> 14:20.992
I <i> am</i> right.

14:25.289 --> 14:27.455
But I'm glad
to be sitting here with you.

14:27.455 --> 14:29.621
Feels right.

14:30.951 --> 14:35.612
Feels like
we're...Going somewhere.

14:35.614 --> 14:39.277
Everything that is good
between men and women

14:39.277 --> 14:41.533
Was written in mud.

14:41.542 --> 14:42.739
And butter.

14:42.740 --> 14:44.367
And barbecue sauce.

14:44.372 --> 14:45.570
You know?
No.

14:47.304 --> 14:50.967
Paula deen said that to me
in a dream I had one time.

14:50.967 --> 14:52.863
Who's paula deen?

14:52.865 --> 14:54.891
Oh, she's a chef on tv.

14:54.896 --> 14:56.892
Well, she <i> was.</i>

14:56.894 --> 14:59.320
Chefs are on tv now,
for some reason.

14:59.326 --> 15:00.523
Mm.

15:00.524 --> 15:02.181
People eat it up.

15:02.190 --> 15:06.721
Anyway, she's just a big ol'
ham hock out of albany, g.A.

15:06.718 --> 15:09.214
She makes southern food
for yankees.

15:09.217 --> 15:11.283
My point is,
in my dream,

15:11.282 --> 15:13.947
I'm white-water rafting
with her, for some reason,

15:13.946 --> 15:17.179
And, um,
she said that to me...

15:17.176 --> 15:20.400
Right before she...
Touched my hamster.

15:21.937 --> 15:24.901
[ laughing ]
but it stuck with me, you know?

15:24.902 --> 15:27.627
It's the only thing from a dream
that ever has.

15:27.633 --> 15:29.789
Do you dream often?

15:29.797 --> 15:31.863
No. Almost never.

15:31.862 --> 15:35.465
I think I sleep more soundly
than anybody I ever met.

15:35.459 --> 15:37.386
In fact, I <i> know</i> I do.

15:39.587 --> 15:42.352
Now, you seem the type
that does a lot of dreaming.

15:42.353 --> 15:45.158
Well, sometimes.

15:45.151 --> 15:47.406
You wake up
and think about them?

15:47.414 --> 15:49.710
Seems like a waste of time
to me.

15:49.713 --> 15:51.669
A waste to think on them?

15:51.677 --> 15:55.340
Once you're awake and walking
around in the real world, yeah.

15:55.341 --> 15:58.136
I mean, once there are things
to actually take care of.

15:58.139 --> 15:59.336
I don't know.

15:59.337 --> 16:01.433
Trying to find meaning
in them --

16:01.435 --> 16:03.731
Trying to find meaning
in <i> anything.</i>

16:03.733 --> 16:06.657
It's a waste of time, if you
really want to get down to it.

16:06.663 --> 16:08.460
So life's meaningless?

16:10.459 --> 16:11.757
<i> Whose</i> life?

16:11.759 --> 16:13.854
Anybody's life,
I suppose.

16:13.857 --> 16:16.323
Isn't that
what you're saying?

16:18.719 --> 16:21.783
Damn, man, you twist things
around like a woman.

16:30.241 --> 16:32.846
Wynn was mad.

16:32.840 --> 16:34.237
Wasn't she?

16:34.238 --> 16:36.863
She all corporate,
you know?

16:36.869 --> 16:38.766
She'll be all right.

16:38.768 --> 16:43.289
Yeah, but I don't like
being like that.

16:51.521 --> 16:54.076
It's been too long
since I smoked.

16:54.087 --> 16:56.612
Exactly -- too long.

16:56.617 --> 16:59.312
No, too long
to do it again.

16:59.315 --> 17:01.251
That'd put me on my ass.

17:01.246 --> 17:04.710
That such a bad thing --
out your head and on your ass?

17:10.405 --> 17:12.431
Can't believe this.

17:12.436 --> 17:14.532
32 years old.

17:18.364 --> 17:21.727
Smoking weed
in the thrifty town parking lot

17:21.728 --> 17:23.753
Where I actually
friggin' work.

17:25.159 --> 17:28.183
How did this happen?

17:30.553 --> 17:33.148
Mm-hmm.

17:33.151 --> 17:35.407
There it is.

17:42.574 --> 17:44.031
Mm.

17:46.271 --> 17:48.437
Just follow
the shiny metal things.

17:50.036 --> 17:52.202
After you, my lady.

17:58.793 --> 18:01.717
I've never bought tires
before.

18:01.724 --> 18:05.158
They've always
just...Been there.

18:11.015 --> 18:13.451
The register used to be
right here.

18:13.447 --> 18:15.373
Mm.

18:15.379 --> 18:17.675
Dad would keep one
of those big-ass metal
flashlights right here,

18:17.677 --> 18:19.703
Just in case he'd need
to take a swing at anyone.

18:23.071 --> 18:27.004
Check in with me next week.
I should have that in for you.

18:27.002 --> 18:29.627
Thank you
for shopping at paulie tire.

18:29.632 --> 18:32.097
I hope
you come back again.

18:32.097 --> 18:33.694
Bye.

18:33.695 --> 18:35.152
Amantha?

18:35.160 --> 18:36.498
Hey.

18:36.493 --> 18:38.758
What are --
what are y'all up to today?

18:38.757 --> 18:41.981
Hey, teddy.
Hope we're not bothering you.

18:41.988 --> 18:44.024
Well, I can't imagine
you're here for tires.

18:44.019 --> 18:45.546
Hey!

18:45.551 --> 18:48.186
Congratulations again
about the baby.

18:48.182 --> 18:50.009
Oh.
Seriously.

18:50.014 --> 18:51.541
Thank you. Yeah.

18:51.546 --> 18:54.540
this is alesha.

18:54.543 --> 18:57.637
And this is
the tire store.

19:04.633 --> 19:06.030
I'm the stepbrother.

19:06.032 --> 19:07.130
Nice to meet you.

19:07.131 --> 19:08.458
Nice to meet you.

19:08.463 --> 19:10.260
We'll get out of your hair
in just a second.

19:10.262 --> 19:13.056
I just wanted
to show her around.

19:13.059 --> 19:15.515
I haven't been here
in so long.

19:15.524 --> 19:18.119
It smells the same.

19:19.986 --> 19:22.681
It's a good smell.

19:22.684 --> 19:25.009
I think about that a lot.

19:25.014 --> 19:27.050
Always smells
the dang same.

19:27.046 --> 19:28.973
Hmm.

19:32.007 --> 19:34.073
I told alesha

19:34.073 --> 19:38.265
That we have the vending machine
to beat all vending machines.

19:38.269 --> 19:39.706
That's true.

19:39.701 --> 19:42.526
We have the chocolate-
and-peanut-butter twix,

19:42.532 --> 19:44.129
So...

19:48.359 --> 19:49.656
She'd like the keys.

19:49.659 --> 19:52.384
Oh. Yeah.
All right.

19:53.488 --> 19:56.382
It's like wonka's factory,
but with rims.

19:57.685 --> 19:59.282
Thank you, teddy.

20:00.914 --> 20:02.152
No problem.

20:02.147 --> 20:04.473
okay.

20:11.572 --> 20:14.097
What would you like?
Number 4, please.

20:14.103 --> 20:16.199
Ahhh!

20:16.201 --> 20:18.028
Here you go.

20:18.033 --> 20:20.568
Okay, okay.
I would like that one, too.

20:30.953 --> 20:32.220
Good afternoon,
mr. Stern.

20:32.219 --> 20:33.577
Good afternoon.

20:33.585 --> 20:36.140
I am on a panel
in half an hour.

20:36.149 --> 20:38.554
Need to do
a little cramming.

20:38.547 --> 20:42.470
I'm sorry -- I don't have
much time to help you prep.

20:42.477 --> 20:45.112
I'm supposed to be on a plane
in a couple of hours.

20:45.108 --> 20:46.575
This is
nothing official yet,

20:46.573 --> 20:48.469
But I asked you
to meet me here today

20:48.471 --> 20:50.497
Because
I am now willing --

20:50.502 --> 20:52.898
Begrudgingly,
but willing --

20:52.901 --> 20:55.466
To discuss the possibility of
a plea deal for daniel holden.

21:02.524 --> 21:04.490
I'm all ears.

21:04.489 --> 21:08.152
Time served plus 10,
15 more probation.

21:08.153 --> 21:09.551
He's not doing more time.

21:09.552 --> 21:11.548
One way or another,
he's going back inside, jon.

21:11.550 --> 21:14.145
Only thing left to discuss
is how long.

21:14.148 --> 21:15.974
10 years is
not a discussion.

21:15.979 --> 21:17.846
How about life?

21:17.845 --> 21:20.340
If you really wanted
to go to trial, you
wouldn't be offering --

21:20.342 --> 21:23.007
I'm not scared
to go back to trial.

21:23.006 --> 21:24.503
That dna's out there now.

21:24.505 --> 21:27.070
Gonna be hard to answer
for that -- multiple samples.

21:27.069 --> 21:29.864
And he confessed --
on the record.

21:29.867 --> 21:32.492
And it's gonna be hard to argue
that it was coerced

21:32.498 --> 21:34.594
Above the sound
of the tape rolling --

21:34.596 --> 21:37.031
The sound of him
saying that he did it.

21:37.027 --> 21:39.322
What if we get that confession
thrown out?

21:44.085 --> 21:46.820
If you think
I see zero chance

21:46.818 --> 21:48.914
Of getting another conviction
at trial,

21:48.916 --> 21:50.912
I'm here to dissuade you
of that notion.

21:50.914 --> 21:52.581
You and your client
should be terrified

21:52.579 --> 21:54.505
Of stepping foot
in a courtroom.

